-- EasyJet leads European equity bounce after guidance hike
-- 
-- Fri Oct 03, 2014 03:09AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 3 (Reuters) - European equity indexes bounced from "oversold" territory on Friday after their steepest falls in several months, with British low-cost airline easyJet <EZJ.L> the biggest gainer after raising its profit forecast.

Shares in easyJet rose 4.2 percent to the top of the pan-European FTSEurofirst 300 index <.FTEU3>, which was up 0.6 percent at 1,343.28 points at 0707 GMT. [ID:nFWN0RW028] Britain's FTSE <.FTSE> was up 0.8 percent while France's CAC <.FCHI> rose 0.7 percent. Both closed in "oversold" territory on Thursday based on their 7-day Relative Strength Index, a momentum indicator which compares the magnitude of recent gains to recent losses.